      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Validate MXC SDK 0.7.0 on Windows build 26200.8728",
        "body": "Tracking issue: #784\nDepends on: #785\nFollowed by: #787\n\nContributor-fork note: this branch is stacked on the PR1 commit, but the PR targets `main` because the PR1 base branch exists in the contributor fork, not in the upstream repository. After PR1 is merged or maintainers provide a preferred upstream base branch, this PR can be rebased/retargeted so the review diff only contains the MXC changes.\n\n## Summary\n\nThis PR updates the Windows MXC dependency and availability gate for explicit build/UBR validation:\n\n- Update `@microsoft/mxc-sdk` from `0.6.1` to `0.7.0`.\n- Replace the single hardcoded supported Windows build with an explicit temporary processcontainer support table.\n- Add processcontainer support for Windows build `26200.8728+`.\n- Preserve processcontainer support for Windows build `26300.8289+`.\n- Keep `isolation_session` separately gated to `26300.8553+`, matching SDK `0.7.0` documentation/source.\n- Emit MXC config schema `0.7.0-alpha` for SDK `0.7.0`.\n- Keep AppContainer-DACL fallback compatible by avoiding protected PATH-directory grants, omitting nonexistent denied-path roots, and granting only backend-safe PATH directories.\n- Bootstrap `TEMP`, `TMP`, `TMPDIR`, and `PATH` inside the launched shell because non-empty MXC `process.env` is not usable on this backend.\n- Preserve the compatibility host-fallback default when MXC is unavailable.\n- Add strict fail-closed behavior behind explicit `SystemRunBlockHostFallbackWhenMxcUnavailable=true`.\n- Reject custom `system.run` environment variables before fallback while sandboxing is enabled, so unsupported custom-env requests cannot bypass MXC policy through compatibility fallback.\n- Keep MXC omitted-shell execution on `cmd` for this processcontainer/AppContainer-DACL tier; normal uncontained host fallback still resolves through the host runner.\n- Resolve explicit `shell=\"pwsh\"` to an absolute `pwsh.exe` path before launching with an empty MXC process environment.\n- Update Sandbox page status/InfoBar text so unavailable MXC clearly distinguishes blocked mode, explicit host fallback, and sandbox-off host execution.\n- Add/extend unit and integration coverage for SDK `0.7.0`, build/UBR gates, config generation, fallback compatibility, settings migration, diagnostics, shell resolution, and MXC RW/RO filesystem access.\n\n## Why\n\nThe local machine is Windows Release Preview 25H2 build `26200.8728`. The MXC SDK probe can report usable processcontainer/AppContainer-DACL support locally, but OpenClaw's current availability gate rejects the machine because it only allows build `26300`.\n\nThis PR keeps the gate explicit and narrow. It does not add a broad `>= 26200` rule and does not enable `isolation_session` on `26200`.\n\n## Validation\n\nFinal-head validation for commit `76f9bf39d5c7073fc9775f6e326249f917ef2f71` on Windows build `26200.8728`:\n\n- `OPENCLAW_RUN_INTEGRATION=1 dotnet test ./tests/OpenClaw.Shared.Tests/OpenClaw.Shared.Tests.csproj --no-restore --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~MxcCommandRunnerIntegrationTests|FullyQualifiedName~MxcCommandRunnerTests|FullyQualifiedName~MxcConfigBuilderTests\" --verbosity minimal`: passed, `82` passed, `0` skipped, `0` failed.\n- `openclaw-autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD --engine codex --model gpt-5.5 --thinking high`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings, overall `patch is correct (0.86)`.\n\nEarlier PR2 runtime proof on Windows build `26200.8728` remains relevant for the supported MXC path:\n\n- `wxc-exec --probe` reported `tier=appcontainer-dacl`.\n- Positive temp write passed.\n- Denied-read smoke did not leak denied content.\n- Temporary MCP `system.run` smoke returned `OPENCLAW_SYSTEM_RUN_MXC_OK`.\n- Logs included `[mxc] availability`, `executor=mxc-direct-appc`, `contained=True`, config `version=0.7.0-alpha`, `envKeys=[]`, and `containment=mxc`.\n\n## Behavior Contract\n\nThis PR intentionally preserves the current compatibility posture while making strict behavior explicit:\n\n- MXC available: use contained processcontainer/AppContainer-DACL execution.\n- MXC unavailable with default settings: preserve compatibility host fallback.\n- MXC unavailable with `SystemRunBlockHostFallbackWhenMxcUnavailable=true`: fail closed.\n- Sandbox disabled: explicit host execution.\n\nCustom `system.run` environment variables remain rejected before fallback while sandboxing is enabled, so unsupported custom-env requests cannot bypass MXC policy through compatibility fallback.\n\n## Validation boundaries\n\n- Full Gateway-mode Companion pairing/runtime proof is in PR3.\n- Installed Companion replacement/profile migration proof is not claimed by PR2.\n- Broad full-suite green status is not claimed by PR2.\n- The explicit build/UBR table remains a temporary validation strategy; maintainers may still prefer the separate probe-based MXC availability direction.\n",
        "branch": "feature/mxc-26200-sdk-0-7-validation",
